MiniPerl6 "Perlito" compiler

Go backend

    ...

    The Go release from about 11 Nov 2009 is required. Newer versions may not work.

    See also: Go homepage at http://golang.org

Javascript backend

    Open the file 'perlito.html' in a browser, or browse to:

    http://perlcabal.org/~fglock/perlito.html

    Executing from the command line requires the V8 javascript compiler:

    perl mp6.pl -Bparrot -e 'class Main { say "hello, World!" }'

    See also: V8 homepage at http://code.google.com/apis/v8

Lisp backend

    ... (see util-lisp directory)

Parrot backend

    The parrot backend is not bootstrapped. 
    The perl 5 backend can be used to compile MiniPerl6 to parrot:

    perl mp6.pl -Bparrot -e 'class Main { say "hello, World!" }'

    See also: Parrot homepage at http://www.parrot.org

Perl 5 backend

    perl mp6.pl -e 'class Main { say "hello, World!" }'

    See also: Perl 5 homepage at http://www.perl.org

